                           <locus target="#150rb">f. 150rb</locus>
                           <desc type="PoemArke">A hymn dedicated to ʾAragāwi Manfasawi.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#150rb">150rb</locus>: ሰላም፡ ለዮሐንስ፡ እምብዝኃ፡ አንክሮ፡ ወተደሞ፨
                              ነጽሮተ፡ ሥሉስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ከመ፡ ማዕበለ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘያሠጥሞ፨ 
                              ሶበ፡ ኂርውናሁ፡ ነጸሩ፡ ወዘዚአሁ፡ አርምሞ፨
                              እንዘ፡ ውእቱ፡ ወሬዛ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ያብጽሕ፡ ዓቅሞ፨ 
                              አረጋዊ፡ መንፈሳዊ፡ ሰመይዎ፡ ስሞ፨</q>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#150rb">150rb</locus>: Hail to Yoḥannǝs from much of
                              admiration and wonder. Whom the vision of the Trinity submerged like a
                              wave of the sea. When they saw his benevolence and his quietness While
                              he was young and had not grown up yet He was called Spiritual
                              Elder</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#150rb">f. 150rb</locus>
                           <desc type="Unclear">A hymn dedicated to ʾAragāwi Manfasawi.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#150rb">150rb</locus>: ጳራቅሊጦስ፡ መንፈሰ፡ ትንቢት፡ ለናሆም፡ ዘሐወፆ፨
                              መጳራቅሊጦስ፡ መብረቅ፡ ለጳውሎስ፡ ዘአደንግፆ፨ መራኁተ፡ ስምዖን፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ጳራ፡ ፈታሔ፡ ማዕፆ፨ ለአረጋዊ፡
                              መንፈሳዊ፡ ያርኅወኒ፡ አንቀጾ፨ ስብሐተ፡ መልክዑ፡ እነጽር፡ ወፍሡሐ፡ ገጾ፨</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#150rb">150rb</locus>: Paraclete, the Spirit of
                              prophecy who visited Nahom, Paraclete who terrified Paul with a
                              lightening, With the key of Simon Peter, the guardian of the gate,
                              Paraclete, May he open the gate for Spiritual Elder, So that I could
                              see his glorious appearance and his joyful face.</q>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus from="150va" to="151rb">ff. 150va-151rb</locus>
                           <desc type="LandGrant">Register of land plots (?), in Amharic and Gǝʿǝz, in two parts.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> አፄ፡ ሶሎሞን፡ የፋሲለደስ፡ የሰጡት፡ ኍልቁ፡
                              ምድር፡ ዘሀሎ፡ በጉንትር፡ ፮ ገመድ፡ የተክለ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/></q>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Amharic and Gǝʿǝz ʾandǝmta-commentaries and glosses
                           written in the margins throughout the text.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>The introduction and
                           discourses nr: 2, 7, 8, 15, discourse on <locus target="#57rb">57rb</locus> contain a prayer distinguished from the main text with a
                           word "ṣalot" in red ink. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc> Discourse 17 contains parts called
                           ḥatäta (‘question’) and täśäṭwo (‘answer’) written in red ink. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc><locus target="#151v">151v</locus>: The Trinitarian formula with the
                           beginning of Maṣḥafa Ṭomar; </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>Writing exercises</desc></item>
